To-Do List App (CLI)

Description:
This Python program is a Command Line To-Do List App that helps users add, view, remove, and mark tasks as completed. It uses a loop-driven menu that allows users to interact with their to-do list until they decide to exit.
How It Works:
The program starts with an empty list of tasks.
Each task is stored as a dictionary with a name and completion status.
Users can:
1.Add new tasks
2.View all tasks
3.Mark tasks as complete
4.Delete tasks
The program runs in a loop until the user chooses to exit.
